  "output": "## Test Coverage Analysis — jobsquare\n\nNo test suite exists yet (no `tests/` dir, no pytest in `requirements.txt`). This is a from-scratch gap analysis across all 7 modules (1,505 LOC). I'll flag genuine correctness bugs I found while reading, since those are the highest-value gaps to cover.\n\n### Setup needed first\n\n```\n# requirements-dev.txt\npytest>=8.0\npytest-asyncio>=0.24\nrespx>=0.21          # mocks httpx transport — fetchers.py is built for this (injectable client)\nfreezegun>=1.5        # for _now()/posted_at time-dependent tests\n```\n\n---\n\n## 1. Bugs found (not just gaps — these will fail once tests exist)\n\n**`models.py:30` — `parse_posted_at` uncaught `OverflowError`/`OSError`.** The numeric-epoch branch calls `datetime.fromtimestamp(n, tz=...)` with no bounds check. A malformed/garbage numeric string (e.g. a source sending `\"99999999999999999999\"`) raises `OverflowError`/`OSError`, uncaught, propagating through `Job.posted_dt` into `filters.match()` — one bad job can crash a whole filter pass.\n\n**`pipeline.py:17` — `load_config` crashes on empty YAML.** `yaml.safe_load(f)` returns `None` for an empty file; `cfg.setdefault(...)` on `None` raises `AttributeError`. An empty `sources.yaml` (easy to create by accident) kills the pipeline with a confusing stack trace.\n\n**`fetchers.py:37-41` — `_request` retries non-retryable errors.** `r.raise_for_status()` on a 404/401/403 raises `httpx.HTTPStatusError`, which is caught by the *same* `except (httpx.TransportError, httpx.HTTPStatusError)` clause used for retryable 429/5xx. A permanent client error (bad company slug, revoked token) gets retried 4x with backoff instead of failing fast — wastes ~30s per bad source and pollutes `fetch_all`'s per-source error log with a misleading \"failed after retries\" message for what was actually an instant 404.\n\n**`models.py:66-69` — `content_hash` excludes `salary_range`, `employment_type`, `posted_at`.** If a listed job's salary range or employment type changes but title/location/url/department don't, `Store.diff()` won't detect it as \"changed\" — no notification fires. May be intentional (avoid noise from frequently-touched fields) but is undocumented and untested; worth a regression test either way.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Per-module gaps + skeletons\n\n### `models.py`\n\n```python\n# tests/test_models.py\nimport pytest\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\nfrom models import Job, parse_posted_at\n\nclass TestParsePostedAt:\n    def test_empty_and_none_return_none(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"\") is None\n\n    def test_lever_milliseconds_epoch(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"1643241332430\")\n        assert dt == datetime.fromtimestamp(1643241332.430, tz=timezone.utc)\n\n    def test_seconds_epoch_under_1e12_boundary(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"1643241332\")  # 10 digits, should NOT be treated as ms\n        assert dt.year == 2022\n\n    def test_iso8601_with_z_suffix(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"2024-01-15T10:00:00Z\")\n        assert dt.tzinfo is not None\n\n    def test_iso8601_naive_gets_utc_attached(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"2024-01-15T10:00:00\")\n        assert dt.tzinfo == timezone.utc\n\n    def test_unparseable_prose_returns_none(self):\n        # Workday sends \"Posted 3 Days Ago\" — must not raise\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"Posted 3 Days Ago\") is None\n\n    def test_negative_numeric_string(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"-100\")\n        assert dt is not None\n\n    def test_extreme_numeric_string_does_not_raise(self):\n        # GAP/BUG: currently raises OverflowError — should return None\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"99999999999999999999\") is None\n\nclass TestJob:\n    def _job(self, **kw):\n        defaults = dict(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\",\n                         title=\"Engineer\", url=\"https://x/1\")\n        return Job(**{**defaults, **kw})\n\n    def test_key_format(self):\n        assert self._job().key == \"greenhouse:acme:1\"\n\n    def test_content_hash_changes_on_title(self):\n        a, b = self._job(), self._job(title=\"Senior Engineer\")\n        assert a.content_hash != b.content_hash\n\n    def test_content_hash_stable_on_salary_only_change(self):\n        # documents current (possibly unintended) behavior\n        a = self._job(salary_range=\"100k\")\n        b = self._job(salary_range=\"200k\")\n        assert a.content_hash == b.content_hash\n\n    def test_posted_dt_delegates_to_parser(self):\n        j = self._job(posted_at=\"1700000000\")\n        assert j.posted_dt is not None\n\n    def test_to_row_excludes_raw_includes_key_and_hash(self):\n        row = self._job(raw={\"secret\": 1}).to_row()\n        assert \"raw\" not in row\n        assert \"key\" in row and \"content_hash\" in row\n```\n\n### `filters.py`\n\n```python\n# tests/test_filters.py\nimport pytest\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta, timezone\nfrom models import Job\nfrom filters import match, filter_jobs\n\ndef _job(title=\"Backend Engineer\", dept=\"Eng\", loc=\"Remote - US\", posted_at=\"\"):\n    return Job(source=\"x\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=title,\n               url=\"u\", department=dept, location=loc, posted_at=posted_at)\n\nclass TestMatch:\n    def test_no_filters_passes(self):\n        assert match(_job()) is True\n\n    def test_include_keyword_hit_and_miss(self):\n        assert match(_job(title=\"Backend Engineer\"), include=[\"backend\"]) is True\n        assert match(_job(title=\"Frontend Engineer\"), include=[\"backend\"]) is False\n\n    def test_exclude_takes_priority_over_include(self):\n        j = _job(title=\"Senior Backend Engineer Intern\")\n        assert match(j, include=[\"backend\"], exclude=[\"intern\"]) is False\n\n    def test_word_boundary_prevents_substring_false_positive(self):\n        # \"eng\" should not match \"engineering\" via naive substring, but should via \\b at word start\n        j = _job(title=\"Engineering Manager\")\n        assert match(j, exclude=[\"eng\"]) is True  # \"eng\" is not a whole word here — must NOT exclude\n        # NOTE: verify actual intended semantics; this asserts current \\b behavior\n\n    def test_regex_special_chars_in_keyword_are_escaped(self):\n        j = _job(title=\"C++ Developer\")\n        assert match(j, include=[\"C++\"]) is True  # must not raise re.error\n\n    def test_locations_substring_case_insensitive(self):\n        assert match(_job(loc=\"Seattle, WA\"), locations=[\"seattle\"]) is True\n        assert match(_job(loc=\"Austin, TX\"), locations=[\"seattle\"]) is False\n\n    def test_cutoff_drops_old_confirmed_dates(self):\n        old = (datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=30)).isoformat()\n        cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=7)\n        assert match(_job(posted_at=old), cutoff=cutoff) is False\n\n    def test_cutoff_keeps_unparseable_dates(self):\n        cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=7)\n        assert match(_job(posted_at=\"Posted 3 Days Ago\"), cutoff=cutoff) is True\n\n    def test_empty_include_list_is_treated_as_no_filter(self):\n        assert match(_job(), include=[]) is True\n\nclass TestFilterJobs:\n    def test_max_age_days_filters_list(self):\n        old = _job(posted_at=(datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=10)).isoformat())\n        new = _job(posted_at=datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat())\n        out = filter_jobs([old, new], {\"max_age_days\": 5})\n        assert out == [new]\n\n    def test_no_rules_returns_all(self):\n        jobs = [_job(), _job(external_id=\"2\")]\n        assert filter_jobs(jobs, {}) == jobs\n\n    def test_max_age_days_as_float_string(self):\n        # rules typically come from YAML — could be \"3.5\"\n        out = filter_jobs([_job()], {\"max_age_days\": \"3.5\"})\n        assert isinstance(out, list)\n```\n\n### `pipeline.py` (integration-shaped — mock the collaborators)\n\n```python\n# tests/test_pipeline.py\nimport pytest\nfrom unittest.mock import AsyncMock, patch\nimport pipeline\n\ndef test_load_config_defaults(tmp_path):\n    p = tmp_path / \"s.yaml\"\n    p.write_text(\"sources: []\\n\")\n    cfg = pipeline.load_config(p)\n    assert cfg[\"filters\"] == {} and cfg[\"db\"] == \"jobs.db\" and cfg[\"concurrency\"] == 8\n\ndef test_load_config_empty_file_raises_or_is_handled(tmp_path):\n    # GAP/BUG: yaml.safe_load('') -> None -> cfg.setdefault raises AttributeError\n    p = tmp_path / \"empty.yaml\"\n    p.write_text(\"\")\n    with pytest.raises(AttributeError):\n        pipeline.load_config(p)   # once fixed, assert it returns defaults instead\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_dry_run_skips_store_and_dispatch(tmp_path):\n    cfg_path = tmp_path / \"s.yaml\"\n    cfg_path.write_text(f\"sources: []\\ndb: {tmp_path/'jobs.db'}\\n\")\n    with patch(\"pipeline.fetch_all\", new=AsyncMock(return_value=[])), \\\n         patch(\"pipeline.dispatch\") as mock_dispatch:\n        result = await pipeline.run(cfg_path, dry_run=True)\n    assert result == {\"matched\": 0, \"new\": 0, \"changed\": 0}\n    mock_dispatch.assert_not_called()\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_run_persists_and_dispatches(tmp_path):\n    # fetch_all -> filter_jobs -> Store.diff -> dispatch, full wiring\n    ...\n\ndef test_run_sync_wraps_asyncio_run(tmp_path):\n    with patch(\"pipeline.run\", new=AsyncMock(return_value={\"matched\": 0, \"new\": 0, \"changed\": 0})):\n        assert pipeline.run_sync(tmp_path / \"s.yaml\") == {\"matched\": 0, \"new\": 0, \"changed\": 0}\n```\n\n### `store.py`\n\n```python\n# tests/test_store.py\nimport sqlite3\nimport pytest\nfrom store import Store\nfrom models import Job\n\ndef _job(external_id=\"1\", title=\"Engineer\", **kw):\n    return Job(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=external_id,\n               title=title, url=\"u\", **kw)\n\nclass TestDiff:\n    def test_new_job_is_inserted_and_returned_as_new(self, tmp_path):\n        with Store(tmp_path / \"t.db\") as s:\n            new, changed = s.diff([_job()])\n            assert len(new) == 1 and changed == []\n            assert s.count() == 1\n\n    def test_unchanged_job_on_second_run_is_neither(self, tmp_path):\n        db = tmp_path / \"t.db\"\n        with Store(db) as s:\n            s.diff([_job()])\n        with Store(db) as s:\n            new, changed = s.diff([_job()])\n            assert new == [] and changed == []\n\n    def test_changed_content_hash_flags_changed(self, tmp_path):\n        db = tmp_path / \"t.db\"\n        with Store(db) as s:\n            s.diff([_job(title=\"Engineer\")])\n        with Store(db) as s:\n            new, changed = s.diff([_job(title=\"Senior Engineer\")])\n            assert new == [] and len(changed) == 1\n\n    def test_duplicate_keys_within_single_batch(self, tmp_path):\n        # GAP: two Job objects with the same key in one fetch batch —\n        # verify no IntegrityError and diff() behaves sanely\n        with Store(tmp_path / \"t.db\") as s:\n            new, changed = s.diff([_job(title=\"A\"), _job(title=\"B\")])\n            assert len(new) + len(changed) >= 1  # document actual behavior\n\nclass TestMeta:\n    def test_get_meta_missing_key_returns_none(self, tmp_path):\n        with Store(tmp_path / \"t.db\") as s:\n            assert s.get_meta(\"last_scan\") is None\n\n    def test_set_meta_then_get_roundtrip(self, tmp_path):\n        with Store(tmp_path / \"t.db\") as s:\n            s.set_meta(\"last_scan\", \"2026-01-01T00:00:00+00:00\")\n            assert s.get_meta(\"last_scan\") == \"2026-01-01T00:00:00+00:00\"\n\n    def test_set_meta_upserts_on_conflict(self, tmp_path):\n        with Store(tmp_path / \"t.db\") as s:\n            s.set_meta(\"k\", \"v1\")\n            s.set_meta(\"k\", \"v2\")\n            assert s.get_meta(\"k\") == \"v2\"\n\nclass TestMigration:\n    def test_old_schema_without_salary_range_gets_migrated(self, tmp_path):\n        db = tmp_path / \"old.db\"\n        conn = sqlite3.connect(db)\n        conn.executescript(\"\"\"\n            CREATE TABLE jobs (key TEXT PRIMARY KEY, source TEXT, company TEXT,\n              external_id TEXT, title TEXT, url TEXT, location TEXT, department TEXT,\n              employment_type TEXT, posted_at TEXT, content_hash TEXT,\n              first_seen TEXT, last_seen TEXT);\n        \"\"\")\n        conn.commit(); conn.close()\n        with Store(db) as s:\n            cols = {r[\"name\"] for r in s.conn.execute(\"PRAGMA table_info(jobs)\")}\n            assert \"salary_range\" in cols\n\nclass TestAddedSince:\n    def test_ordering_and_strict_greater_than(self, tmp_path):\n        ...\n\ndef test_context_manager_closes_connection(tmp_path):\n    s = Store(tmp_path / \"t.db\")\n    with s:\n        pass\n    with pytest.raises(sqlite3.ProgrammingError):\n        s.conn.execute(\"SELECT 1\")\n```\n\n### `notify.py`\n\n```python\n# tests/test_notify.py\nimport pytest\nfrom unittest.mock import patch, MagicMock\nimport notify\nfrom models import Job\n\ndef _job(**kw):\n    return Job(source=\"x\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"Engineer\",\n               url=\"https://x/1\", **kw)\n\nclass TestNotifyConsole:\n    def test_prints_no_fresh_listings_when_empty(self, capsys):\n        notify.notify_console([], [])\n        assert \"No fresh listings\" in capsys.readouterr().out\n\n    def test_prints_new_and_changed_sections(self, capsys):\n        notify.notify_console([_job()], [_job(external_id=\"2\")])\n        out = capsys.readouterr().out\n        assert \"NEW\" in out and \"UPDATED\" in out\n\nclass TestNotifySlack:\n    def test_noop_without_env_var(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.delenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", raising=False)\n        with patch(\"httpx.post\") as p:\n            notify.notify_slack([_job()], [])\n            p.assert_not_called()\n\n    def test_noop_with_no_jobs_even_if_url_set(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", \"https://hooks/x\")\n        with patch(\"httpx.post\") as p:\n            notify.notify_slack([], [])\n            p.assert_not_called()\n\n    def test_posts_when_url_and_jobs_present(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", \"https://hooks/x\")\n        with patch(\"httpx.post\") as p:\n            notify.notify_slack([_job(salary_range=\"100k\")], [])\n            p.assert_called_once()\n            assert \"100k\" in p.call_args.kwargs[\"json\"][\"text\"]\n\nclass TestNotifySms:\n    def test_noop_unless_all_four_env_vars_set(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID\", \"sid\")\n        monkeypatch.delenv(\"TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN\", raising=False)\n        with patch(\"httpx.post\") as p:\n            notify.notify_sms([_job()], [])\n            p.assert_not_called()\n\n    def test_body_truncates_at_limit(self):\n        jobs = [_job(external_id=str(i), title=f\"Role {i}\") for i in range(12)]\n        body = notify._sms_body(jobs, [], limit=8)\n        assert \"+4 more\" in body\n\n    def test_body_is_ascii_only(self):\n        # regression guard: non-GSM chars force costly UCS-2 SMS segments\n        body = notify._sms_body([_job(title=\"Café Role\")], [])\n        # documents current behavior — title chars pass through unescaped;\n        # decide whether non-ASCII should be stripped/transliterated\n        assert isinstance(body, str)\n\n    def test_raises_on_twilio_error_response(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID\", \"sid\")\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN\", \"tok\")\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"TWILIO_FROM\", \"+1\")\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"TWILIO_TO\", \"+2\")\n        resp = MagicMock()\n        resp.raise_for_status.side_effect = Exception(\"boom\")\n        with patch(\"httpx.post\", return_value=resp):\n            with pytest.raises(Exception):\n                notify.notify_sms([_job()], [])\n\nclass Test