        "title": "1. Bugs found (not just gaps — these will fail once tests exist)",
        "content": "\n**`models.py:30` — `parse_posted_at` uncaught `OverflowError`/`OSError`.** The numeric-epoch branch calls `datetime.fromtimestamp(n, tz=...)` with no bounds check. A malformed/garbage numeric string (e.g. a source sending `\"99999999999999999999\"`) raises `OverflowError`/`OSError`, uncaught, propagating through `Job.posted_dt` into `filters.match()` — one bad job can crash a whole filter pass.\n\n**`pipeline.py:17` — `load_config` crashes on empty YAML.** `yaml.safe_load(f)` returns `None` for an empty file; `cfg.setdefault(...)` on `None` raises `AttributeError`. An empty `sources.yaml` (easy to create by accident) kills the pipeline with a confusing stack trace.\n\n**`fetchers.py:37-41` — `_request` retries non-retryable errors.** `r.raise_for_status()` on a 404/401/403 raises `httpx.HTTPStatusError`, which is caught by the *same* `except (httpx.TransportError, httpx.HTTPStatusError)` clause used for retryable 429/5xx. A permanent client error (bad company slug, revoked token) gets retried 4x with backoff instead of failing fast — wastes ~30s per bad source and pollutes `fetch_all`'s per-source error log with a misleading \"failed after retries\" message for what was actually an instant 404.\n\n**`models.py:66-69` — `content_hash` excludes `salary_range`, `employment_type`, `posted_at`.** If a listed job's salary range or employment type changes but title/location/url/department don't, `Store.diff()` won't detect it as \"changed\" — no notification fires. May be intentional (avoid noise from frequently-touched fields) but is undocumented and untested; worth a regression test either way.\n\n---\n\n",
        "level": 2
      },
